Details

Job Posting Title:   Test Engineer/Provare Software / Mjukvara level 4 [EE]
Description:   Engineer with Analysis & Verification Competence to Lidar Sensor Team

In our department within Safe Vehicle Automation we are around 160 ambitious and highly skilled engineers creating tomorrow’s platform solutions for our active safety and self-driving vehicles. Our Agile Release Train (ART) Autonomous Drive & Advanced Driver Assistance System Platform develops the complete sensor and software platform for functions such as collision avoidance, automatic parking, autonomous driving. Included in our responsibility is design and verification of state-of-the-art LIDARs, ultrasonic sensors, cameras and radars.

We are now looking for an engineer with experience from Analysis & Verification (A&V) Engineering to our Lidar Sensor team.

What you will do
We want a curious and open-minded team player to be part of our agile development team, someone who is skilled within sensor and system verification.

You will contribute with knowledge from A&V to a cross functional team. The team’s mission is to secure the delivery and quality of sensors into our cars. In our agile teams you should also be flexible to broaden your experience and contributions to system-, software- or hardware engineering.

Typical A&V related tasks could be test case development, performance data collection, SW-testing, integration & BaseTech testing, test documentation as well as fault tracing. We test in rig & on-road environment and you will continuously improve our speed by contributing to test automation and increase our continuous integration.

You should be confident of using Matlab. Experience from Python, C/C++ or C # and communication protocols such as Ethernet are useful. Knowledge from AUTOSAR and ISO26262 are relevant. Continuous integration chains for verification

Do you fit the profile?
To be the right person in this role we see that you have at minimum 3 years of experience within analysis and verification from the automotive sector or other relevant sectors.  Your academic background is a B.Sc. degree, or as meritorious, an M.Sc. degree, within Electrical, Engineering Physics, Mechatronics, Mathematics or equivalent level of education.

Also seen as meritorious is that you have knowledge of AUTOSAR and proven hands-on experience in setting up CI infrastructure for a production grade solution. We are also interested to learn about the products in the market which you have contributed towards.  For this role, we require that you have a valid driver’s licence (B).

As for your personal qualities, we see that you are a driven, methodical and resourceful team player who can deliver the "how" and "what" in dynamic multidisciplinary and multicultural environment. You thrive in managing complexity and bringing engineers together to make a difference in the product. Of course, you are also a good communicator, and have excellent English skills both verbally and in writing.

